      "text": " NORMAL MODE                                                                            ON-PREM OUTAGE (Act 2)                                                      OSD FAILOVER (Act 3)\nCustomer → ARO Route → frontend → api-gateway               Script: 02-failover-onprem.sh                                                   Script: 04-failover-cloud.sh\napi-gateway → Submariner → account-service (on-prem)      1. Remove cloud=on-prem label from ManagedCluster        1. Scale up postgres-core on OSD (replicas=1)\napi-gateway → Submariner → transaction-service                  2. ACM withdraws on-prem ManifestWorks                           2. Patch cloud subscription → lifeboat-placement\n account-service → postgres-core (on-prem, read/write)         3. Scale up postgres-core on ARO (replicas=1)                      3. ACM moves gateway+frontend to OSD\naccount-service → postgres-archive (PII, on-prem)                  4. Gateway detects backend down → limited mode               4. Same limited mode on OSD route\n                                                                          5. Reads from Portworx replica (read-only)\n                                                                          6. PII unavailable (archive is on-prem only)",
      "fontSize": 10,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": " NORMAL MODE                                                                            ON-PREM OUTAGE (Act 2)                                                      OSD FAILOVER (Act 3)\nCustomer → ARO Route → frontend → api-gateway               Script: 02-failover-onprem.sh                                                   Script: 04-failover-cloud.sh\napi-gateway → Submariner → account-service (on-prem)      1. Remove cloud=on-prem label from ManagedCluster        1. Scale up postgres-core on OSD (replicas=1)\napi-gateway → Submariner → transaction-service                  2. ACM withdraws on-prem ManifestWorks                           2. Patch cloud subscription → lifeboat-placement\n account-service → postgres-core (on-prem, read/write)         3. Scale up postgres-core on ARO (replicas=1)                      3. ACM moves gateway+frontend to OSD\naccount-service → postgres-archive (PII, on-prem)                  4. Gateway detects backend down → limited mode               4. Same limited mode on OSD route\n                                                                          5. Reads from Portworx replica (read-only)\n                                                                          6. PII unavailable (archive is on-prem only)",
